# Styling

## Mandatory Standards (MUST)
- Use CSS Modules for all new components
- Avoid global styles except for base theme styling
- Class names should be in kebab-case in CSS modules and camelCase in components (kebab-case to camelCase conversion is handled by Vite during build)
- Avoid deep selector nesting (maximum 3 levels)
- Use CSS variables for colors and sizes from the HRDS UI system

## Recommendations (SHOULD)
- Group styles by components
- Use variables for colors and sizes
- Avoid !important
- Use modern CSS functions (clamp, min, max)
- Optimize animations with will-change and transform

## Examples
```css
/* ✅ Correct (CSS Modules) */
/* ComponentName.module.css */
.button-primary {
  background: var(--hr-color-surface-0);
}

/* ❌ Incorrect */
/* styles.module.css */
.buttonPrimary {
  background: #fff;
}
